# Java Code Rules

1. Write executable and well-commented Java code
2. Follow standard Java naming conventions:
   - Class names: PascalCase
   - Method/variable names: camelCase
   - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
3. Organize classes logically with proper package structure
4. Include appropriate access modifiers (private, public, protected)
5. Document classes and methods with meaningful comments